Copyright (C) 2011 maple (maple@maplef.net)


ABOUT GURU
-----------
guru is a conversational robot -- a computer program you can talk to. 
guru has only been test under ubuntu 10.04 + pidigin 2.7.11, there is no g that 

GET STARTED (Source distribution)
----------------------------------
1. Unzip the archive (you've done that).
2. Edit the guru.ini file to customize your own bot 
3. run "guru.py" in the main guru directory.

ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS
----------------

guru's ai back-end is provided by PyAIML
(http://pyaiml.sourceforge.net), a Python implementation of Dr. Richard S.
Wallace's A.L.I.C.E. system. For more information about the A.L.I.C.E.
Foundation (including information on AIML, the Artificial Intelligence
Markup Language used to program guru's responses), visit the A.L.I.C.E.
homepage at http://www.alicebot.org/. 

Hooray for Python! (http://www.python.org/)

